<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=97564488721166></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97564488721166><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&mid=97564488721166>RE: babien</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=374><span id=Sage>Sapper</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>25 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Nov 30th 11:28 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.93]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Bards share a negative experience modifier with the other Hybrids (Shadowknights, Rangers, Paladins).  Hybrids suffer this because they are so versatile and have a little of the best of thier parent classes.  Rangers = Druid/Warrior, Paladins = Cleric/Warrior, Shadowknights = Necromancer/Warrior.  Bards = Everything ;o)<br><br>I dont know of anyone who says Bards are the hardest to level, that disticntion goes to the Troll Shadowknight as far as I know.  They have the negative exp modifier for Trolls AND the negative exp modifier for Shadowknights. <br>Bards, however, are one of the toughest classes to learn to play correctly.  No other class has to be so nimble fingered and adept at swapping spell(song) lineups as we are.  The poll taken here at Allakhazams listed Enchanters first, and Bards second I believe as the most difficult classes to play well. <br>&nbsp;<br>Sapper Diesalot, At Deaths Door.  "Chuck Berry cant twist this good!"</td></tr>
