	   <tr><td colspan=2>While I don't mind all these postings, all I can say is that it is slightly off. I have played my Bard(half-elf) with his 14x100 penalty with a warrior before with his penalty of 9x120(iksar) My penalty was 140 his 108. We grouped for an entire night together, and both of us dinged at the same exact times twice that night.<br><br>I level 9 he level 8 at the beginning of the night, at the end I dinged into 11, he dinged into 10. <br><br>We went out seperate ways, but what this told me that yes I did take experience "away" from him, but because I was both high level, and had superior equipment, skills, and songs. I helped him more than he helped me at killing mobs, all the while I was taking more experience. This balanced us out, but would not have happened if your information, or rather BLAH's information was correct.<br><br>Perhaps why some people may make the false assumption that hybrids need to play the game more is because alot of time they won't always stay together in a group for long enough to notice, but it does occur, my status as a constant lowbie, but at the same time powerleveler has allowed me to see this.<br><br>Try it out yourself, one of you start a halfling warrior, the other start a Troll shadowknight, group somewhere together, you could both perhaps meet in the commons after you level up a bit, and start grouping together at level 5, don't kill anything when not together, and you will see that you are both leveling at the same rate.<br>&nbsp;<br>Ezzlan 25th ENC Brell<br>Antarius 35th Bard Terris-Thule</td></tr>
