	   <tr><td colspan=2>You can make hotkeys for your primary and off hand slots by clicking and holding the key like you would when putting a skill into your hotkeys.<br><br>Then you make another hotkey for the bag that you keep your weapons and instruments in. I recommend that you keep all your weapons and instruments in one bag so that you don't have to go looking through all of them to find the instrument you want.<br><br>Now when you're opened to the hotkey page that has your hands and instrument/weapon bag in it, you can open the bag and switch instruments right from there (without switching to inventory mode). <br><br>I *highly* suggest that you turn off auto-drop (if you haven't already) or it is only a matter of time before you lose a valuable weapon or instrument.<br><br>If you're asking how to make it switch instruments automatically, you can't (at least not by any way I know of).<br><br>Good luck and happy barding! :)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
