<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=97192476725439></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97192476725439><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&mid=97192476725439>RE: Bocelli</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Oct 18th 11:06 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Right now.  It's a player skill, not a character skill....my suggestion would be to put your songs into hot-keys.  <br>Then you punch the # for the song you want to start singing first,<br>then (once you get good you can modify this step) when the effect comes up, hit the #  for the next song twice - once to turn the last one off, once to turn the new one on.<br>  - you'll need to figure out the timing so that you don't get a "you haven't recovered <br>     yet" message - if you do, just hit the # again and try a little slower next time.<br><br>Repeat as well as you can, rotating back to the first before the effect ends.<br><br><br>Hope this helps.<br><br>Happy Trails.<br><br>Philoscope<br>Bard of the 11th song<br>Teris-Thule<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
